InfoLoop News App

infoLoop is a web-based news application that provides users with the latest news articles from various sources using the GNews API. It is built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, offering a simple and user-friendly interface for browsing trending news.

🚀 Features

Fetches real-time news articles using GNews API

Categorized news sections (e.g., Technology, Business, Sports, Entertainment)

Responsive design for mobile and desktop users

Search functionality to find specific news topics

User-friendly interface with smooth UI/UX

🛠 Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

API: GNews.io

Hosting: (Specify if using Netlify, GitHub Pages, Vercel, etc.)

📦 Installation & Setup

Follow these steps to set up the project locally:

Clone the Repository:

git clone https://github.com/Ayushskull/infoLoop.git
cd infoLoop

Get GNews API Key:

Sign up at GNews.io

Generate an API key

Configure API Key:

Open script.js

Replace’YOUR_API_KEY' with your actual GNews API key:

const API_KEY = 'YOUR_API_KEY';

Run the App:

Simply open index.html in a browser.

Or use a local server like VS Code Live Server.

📌 Usage

Open the app and browse through the latest news.

Click on a news article to read more.

Use the search bar to find news related to specific topics.

🔥 Future Enhancements

Dark mode feature

User authentication for personalized news feed

Bookmarking and saving favorite articles

Multi-language support

